#. <html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><meta content="Pali text from the Mahāsaṅgīti Tipiṭaka Buddhavasse 2500" name="description"><title></title></head><body><div id="text" lang="pli"><section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-np6"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. </p><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs0.3"
msgid "Nissaggiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on relinquishment"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Cīvaravagga"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs0.5"
msgid ""
msgstr "Monks’ Relinquishment"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs0.6"
msgid "6. Aññātakaviññattisikkhāpada"
msgstr "6. The training rule on asking non-relations"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.1.0b"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.211"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-np.6.1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.6.1.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.42"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1974"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

#. VAR: paṭṭo → paṭṭho (s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upanando sakyaputto paṭṭo hoti dhammiṃ kathaṃ "
"kātuṃ."
msgstr "At that time Venerable Upananda the Sakyan was skilled at teaching."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho aññataro seṭṭhiputto yenāyasmā upanando sakyaputto tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "On one occasion the son of a prominent merchant approached Upananda,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.1.4"
msgid ""
"upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed down to him, and sat down to one side."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.43"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.1.5"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho taṃ seṭṭhiputtaṃ āyasmā upanando sakyaputto dhammiyā "
"kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi."
msgstr "And Upananda instructed, inspired, and gladdened him with a teaching."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.1.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so seṭṭhiputto āyasmatā upanandena sakyaputtena dhammiyā kathāya "
"sandassito samādapito samuttejito sampahaṃsito āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ "
"sakyaputtaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "Afterwards that merchant’s son said to Upananda:"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.1.7"
msgid "“vadeyyātha, bhante, yena attho."
msgstr "“Venerable, please tell me what you need."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.1.8"
msgid ""
"Paṭibalā mayaṃ ayyassa dātuṃ yadidaṃ "
"cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhāran”ti."
msgstr "I’m able to give you robe-cloth, almsfood, dwellings, and medicines.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.1.9"
msgid "“Sace me tvaṃ, āvuso, dātukāmosi, ito ekaṃ sāṭakaṃ dehī”ti."
msgstr "“If you wish to give me something, then give me one of your robes.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.1.10"
msgid "“Amhākaṃ kho, bhante, kulaputtānaṃ kismiṃ viya ekasāṭakaṃ gantuṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Venerable, it’s shameful for the son of a good family to walk around in "
"only one robe."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.1.11"
msgid "Āgamehi, bhante, yāva gharaṃ gacchāmi."
msgstr "Please wait until I get back home."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.1.12"
msgid "Gharaṃ gato ito vā ekaṃ sāṭakaṃ pahiṇissāmi ito vā sundarataran”ti."
msgstr "I’ll send you this robe or a better one.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1975"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.1.13"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho āyasmā upanando sakyaputto taṃ seṭṭhiputtaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "A second time"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.1.14"
msgid "“sace me tvaṃ, āvuso, dātukāmosi ito ekaṃ sāṭakaṃ dehī”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.1.15"
msgid ""
"Amhākaṃ kho bhante kulaputtānaṃ kismiṃ viya ekasāṭakaṃ gantuṃ, āgamehi, "
"bhante yāva gharaṃ gacchāmi, gharaṃ gato ito vā ekaṃ sāṭakaṃ pahiṇissāmi ito "
"vā sundarataranti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.1.16"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho āyasmā upanando sakyaputto taṃ seṭṭhiputtaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and a third time Upananda said"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.1.17"
msgid "“sace me tvaṃ, āvuso, dātukāmosi, ito ekaṃ sāṭakaṃ dehī”ti."
msgstr "the same thing to that merchant’s son,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.1.18"
msgid ""
"Amhākaṃ kho, bhante, kulaputtānaṃ kismiṃ viya ekasāṭakaṃ gantuṃ, āgamehi, "
"bhante yāva gharaṃ gacchāmi, gharaṃ gato ito vā ekaṃ sāṭakaṃ pahiṇissāmi ito "
"vā sundarataranti."
msgstr "and he got the same reply."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.44"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.1.19"
msgid ""
"“Kiṃ pana tayā, āvuso, adātukāmena pavāritena yaṃ tvaṃ pavāretvā na desī”ti."
msgstr ""
"He then said, “What’s the point of making an offer if you don’t want to "
"give?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1977"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.1.20"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so seṭṭhiputto āyasmatā upanandena sakyaputtena nippīḷiyamāno ekaṃ "
"sāṭakaṃ datvā agamāsi."
msgstr ""
"Being pressured by Upananda, that merchant’s son gave him one of his robes "
"and left."

#. <a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.6.1.2"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.2.1"
msgid "Manussā taṃ seṭṭhiputtaṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "People asked him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.2.2"
msgid "“kissa tvaṃ, ayyo, ekasāṭako āgacchasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Why, sir, are you walking around in only one robe?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.2.3"
msgid "Atha kho so seṭṭhiputto tesaṃ manussānaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "And he told them what had happened."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.2.4"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People grumbled and complained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.2.5"
msgid "“mahicchā ime samaṇā sakyaputtiyā asantuṭṭhā."
msgstr "“These Sakyan ascetics have great desires; they are not content."

#. VAR: Nayimesaṃ sukarā dhammanimantanāpi kātuṃ → nayime sukarā dhamma­ni­manta­nāya kātuṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.2.6"
msgid "Nayimesaṃ sukarā dhammanimantanāpi kātuṃ."
msgstr "Even to make them an appropriate offer isn’t easy."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.2.7"
msgid ""
"Kathañhi nāma seṭṭhiputtena dhammanimantanāya kayiramānāya sāṭakaṃ "
"gahessantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"How can they take his robe when the merchant’s son was making an appropriate "
"offer?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1978"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.2.8"
msgid ""
"Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.2.9"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.2.10"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized Upananda,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.2.11"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando sakyaputto seṭṭhiputtaṃ cīvaraṃ "
"viññāpessatī”ti."
msgstr "“How can Venerable Upananda ask the merchant’s son for a robe?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1979"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.2.12"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ anekapariyāyena "
"vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing him in many ways, they told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.2.13"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, upananda, seṭṭhiputtaṃ cīvaraṃ viññāpesī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Upananda, that you acted like this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.2.14"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.2.15"
msgid "“Ñātako te, upananda, aññātako”ti?"
msgstr "“Is he a relative of yours?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.2.16"
msgid "“Aññātako, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“No, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.2.17"
msgid ""
"“Aññātako, moghapurisa, aññātakassa na jānāti patirūpaṃ vā appatirūpaṃ vā "
"santaṃ vā asantaṃ vā."
msgstr ""
"“Foolish man, people who are not related don’t know what’s appropriate and "
"what’s inappropriate in dealing with each other, what’s right and what’s "
"wrong."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.2.18"
msgid ""
"Tattha nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, aññātakaṃ seṭṭhiputtaṃ cīvaraṃ viññāpessasi."
msgstr "And still you asked the merchant’s son for a robe."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.45"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.2.19"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.2.20"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.2.20a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1980"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.2.21"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu aññātakaṃ gahapatiṃ vā gahapatāniṃ vā cīvaraṃ viññāpeyya, "
"nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk asks an unrelated layman or laywoman for robe-cloth, he commits "
"an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1981"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs1.2.22"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.212"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.6.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1982"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū sāketā sāvatthiṃ "
"addhānamaggappaṭipannā honti."
msgstr "At that time, while traveling on the main road from Sāketa to Sāvatthī,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.2"
msgid "Antarāmagge corā nikkhamitvā te bhikkhū acchindiṃsu."
msgstr "a number of monks were robbed by bandits."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.3"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū—"
msgstr "Knowing"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.4"
msgid ""
"“bhagavatā paṭikkhittaṃ aññātakaṃ gahapatiṃ vā gahapatāniṃ vā cīvaraṃ "
"viññāpetun”ti,"
msgstr "that the Master had laid down this training rule"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.5"
msgid "kukkuccāyantā na viññāpesuṃ."
msgstr "and being afraid of wrongdoing, they did not ask for robe-cloth."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.6"
msgid "Yathānaggāva sāvatthiṃ gantvā bhikkhū abhivādenti."
msgstr "They walked naked to Sāvatthī and bowed down to the monks."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.7"
msgid "Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "The monks said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.8"
msgid "“sundarā kho ime, āvuso, ājīvakā ye ime bhikkhūsu abhivādentī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“These Ājīvaka ascetics are good people, in that they bow down to the monks.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.9"
msgid "Te evamāhaṃsu—“na mayaṃ, āvuso, ājīvakā,"
msgstr "“We’re not Ājīvakas;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.10"
msgid "bhikkhū mayan”ti."
msgstr "we’re monks!”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.11"
msgid "Bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ upāliṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "And the monks said to Venerable Upāli,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.12"
msgid "“iṅghāvuso upāli, ime anuyuñjāhī”ti."
msgstr "“Upāli, please examine them.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.13"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmatā upālinā anuyuñjiyamānā te bhikkhū etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "The naked monks then told Upāli what had happened,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.14"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā upāli te bhikkhū anuyuñjitvā bhikkhū etadavoca—"
msgstr "and he told the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.15"
msgid "“bhikkhū ime, āvuso."
msgstr "“They are monks."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.16"
msgid "Detha nesaṃ cīvarānī”ti."
msgstr "Give them robes.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.17"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.18"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.19"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma bhikkhū naggā āgacchissanti."
msgstr "“How can monks go naked?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.20"
msgid "Nanu nāma tiṇena vā paṇṇena vā paṭicchādetvā āgantabban”ti."
msgstr "Shouldn’t they have covered up with grass and leaves?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1983"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.21"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū te anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ "
"ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, they told the Master."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.46"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.22"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā "
"bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards he gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.23"
msgid ""
"“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, acchinnacīvarassa vā naṭṭhacīvarassa vā aññātakaṃ "
"gahapatiṃ vā gahapatāniṃ vā cīvaraṃ viññāpetuṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Monks, if a monk’s robes are stolen or destroyed, I allow him to ask an "
"unrelated lay person for robe-cloth."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.47"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.24"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ āvāsaṃ paṭhamaṃ upagacchati, sace tattha hoti saṃghassa vihāracīvaraṃ vā "
"uttarattharaṇaṃ vā bhūmattharaṇaṃ vā bhisicchavi vā, taṃ gahetvā pārupituṃ"
msgstr ""
"At the first monastery where he arrives, if the Order has a monastery robe, "
"a bed sheet, a floor cover, or a pillow case, he should take that and put it "
"on, thinking,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.25"
msgid "‘labhitvā odahissāmī’ti."
msgstr "‘When I get a robe, I’ll return it.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.26"
msgid ""
"No ce hoti saṃghassa vihāracīvaraṃ vā uttarattharaṇaṃ vā bhūmattharaṇaṃ vā "
"bhisicchavi vā tiṇena vā paṇṇena vā paṭicchādetvā āgantabbaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"If there’s none of these things, he should cover up with grass and leaves "
"before going on."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.27"
msgid "na tveva naggena āgantabbaṃ."
msgstr "He should not go on while naked."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.28"
msgid "Yo āgaccheyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he does, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.29"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.29a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1984"></a>
#. <span class="rule">
#. <i lang="pli">Cīvara</i> means both a finished robe and any cloth that can be used to make a robe. Thus I vary my translation depending on the context.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.30"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu aññātakaṃ gahapatiṃ vā gahapatāniṃ vā cīvaraṃ viññāpeyya, "
"aññatra samayā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk asks an unrelated layman or laywoman for robe-cloth, unless there "
"is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and "
"confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.31"
msgid "Tatthāyaṃ samayo—"
msgstr "The appropriate reasons are these:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.32"
msgid "acchinnacīvaro vā hoti bhikkhu naṭṭhacīvaro vā."
msgstr "his robes are stolen or his robes are destroyed.’”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.33"
msgid "Ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs2.34"
msgid "(<em>6</em>:<strong>25</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-np.6.3"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.6.3.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1985"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""
"… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order "
"through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1986"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.1.6"
msgid "Aññātako nāma"
msgstr "Unrelated:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.1.7"
msgid "mātito vā pitito vā yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā asambaddho."
msgstr ""
"anyone who is not a descendant of one’s male ancestors going back seven "
"generations, either on the mother’s side or on the father’s side."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1987"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.1.8"
msgid "Gahapati nāma"
msgstr "A layman:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.1.9"
msgid "yo koci agāraṃ ajjhāvasati."
msgstr "any man who lives in a house."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1988"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.1.10"
msgid "Gahapatānī nāma"
msgstr "A laywoman:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.1.11"
msgid "yā kāci agāraṃ ajjhāvasati."
msgstr "any woman who lives in a house."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.213"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.48"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1989"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.1.12"
msgid "Cīvaraṃ nāma"
msgstr "Robe-cloth:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. The six are linen, cotton, silk, wool, sunn hemp, and hemp; see <ref>Mv.8.3.1</ref>.
#. This means not smaller than 8 by 4 standard (<i lang="pli">sugata</i>) finger-breadths, or 16 by 8 cm; see <ref>Kkh.94.4</ref> and BMC I, pp.565-566.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.1.13"
msgid "channaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ vikappanupagaṃ pacchimaṃ."
msgstr ""
"one of the six kinds of robe-cloth, but not smaller than what can be "
"transferred."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1990"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.1.14"
msgid "Aññatra samayāti"
msgstr "Unless there is an appropriate reason:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.1.15"
msgid "ṭhapetvā samayaṃ."
msgstr "except at an appropriate time."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1991"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.1.16"
msgid "Acchinnacīvaro nāma"
msgstr "His robes are stolen:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.1.17"
msgid ""
"bhikkhussa cīvaraṃ acchinnaṃ hoti rājūhi vā corehi vā dhuttehi vā, yehi "
"kehici vā acchinnaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"a monk’s robe is taken by kings, bandits, scoundrels, or anyone whomsoever."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1992"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.1.18"
msgid "Naṭṭhacīvaro nāma"
msgstr "His robes are destroyed:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.1.19"
msgid ""
"bhikkhussa cīvaraṃ agginā vā daḍḍhaṃ hoti, udakena vā vūḷhaṃ hoti, undūrehi "
"vā upacikāhi vā khāyitaṃ hoti, paribhogajiṇṇaṃ vā hoti."
msgstr ""
"a monk’s robe is burnt by fire, carried away by water, eaten by rats or "
"termites, or worn through use."

#. </span></p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.6.3.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1993"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.2.1"
msgid "Aññatra samayā viññāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ."
msgstr ""
"For the act of asking, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commit an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.2.2"
msgid "Paṭilābhena nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "When he gets the robe-cloth, it becomes subject to relinquishment."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.2.3"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr ""
"The robe-cloth should be relinquished to an Order, a group, or an individual."

#. <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.2.4"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ …"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way. …"

#. <span class="pe"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.2.5"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""
"To be expanded as in <a class=\"cr\" href=\"./pli-tv-bu-vb-np1#23-#29\">"
"Relinquishment 1, paragraphs 13–17</a>, with appropriate substitutions. …"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.2.6"
msgid ""
"idaṃ me, bhante, cīvaraṃ aññātakaṃ gahapatikaṃ, aññatra samayā viññāpitaṃ, "
"nissaggiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘Venerables, this robe-cloth which I received after asking an unrelated lay "
"person without an appropriate reason is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.2.7"
msgid "Imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmīti … pe …"
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’ …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.2.8"
msgid "dadeyyāti … pe …"
msgstr "the Order should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.2.9"
msgid "dadeyyunti … pe …"
msgstr "you should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.2.10"
msgid "āyasmato dammīti."
msgstr "‘I give this robe-cloth back to you.’”"

#. </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.6.3.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1994"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.3.1"
msgid ""
"Aññātake aññātakasaññī aññatra samayā cīvaraṃ viññāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ "
"pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If the person is unrelated and the monk perceives them as unrelated, and he "
"asks them for a robe-cloth, unless there is an appropriate reason, he "
"commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.3.2"
msgid ""
"Aññātake vematiko aññatra samayā cīvaraṃ viññāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If the person is unrelated, but the monk is unsure if they are, and he asks "
"them for a robe-cloth, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an "
"offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.3.3"
msgid ""
"Aññātake ñātakasaññī aññatra samayā cīvaraṃ viññāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ "
"pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If the person is unrelated, but the monk perceives them as related, and he "
"asks them for a robe-cloth, unless there is an appropriate reason, he "
"commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1995"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.3.4"
msgid "Ñātake aññātakasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If the person is related, but the monk perceives them as unrelated, he "
"commit an offense of wrong conduct."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.49"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.3.5"
msgid "Ñātake vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If the person is related, but the monk is unsure if they are, he commit an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.3.6"
msgid "Ñātake ñātakasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If the person is related and the monk perceives them as related, there is no "
"offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.4.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.6.3.4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1996"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.4.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.4.2"
msgid "samaye,"
msgstr "if there is an appropriate reason;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.4.3"
msgid "ñātakānaṃ,"
msgstr "if he asks relatives;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.4.4"
msgid "pavāritānaṃ,"
msgstr "if he asks those who have given an invitation;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.4.5"
msgid "aññassatthāya,"
msgstr "if he asks for the benefit of someone else;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.4.6"
msgid "attano dhanena,"
msgstr "if it is by means of his own property;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.4.7"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.4.8"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="24"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1997"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:pts-cs3.4.9"
msgid "Aññātakaviññattisikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr "The sixth rule, the training rule on asking non-relations, is finished."

